---
description: MCP tool action classification and approval policy
alwaysApply: true
---

The canonical MCP policy lives in `docs/MCP_WORKFLOW.md`, MCP Tool Policy. Classify every MCP action before calling it:

- **READ** — may run without approval (inspect schema, search files, read PRs).
- **REVERSIBLE WRITE** — state the target and intended change before executing (create a branch, update a draft, modify a development record).
- **HIGH IMPACT** — explicit user approval required (deploy, delete, production database write, credential change, force push, destructive migration, mass update).

Standing principles: read before write; use the narrowest tool available, never a broader one when a narrower exists; never silently switch from a development target to a production target; never expose credential values (`docs/SECURITY.md`).
